<center> <h1> Lab 2</h1></center>

<hr WIDTH="100%">

<h3>Lab Assignment:</h3>

Note: Everything in this lab assignment, unless otherwise stated, must be performed on the <sc>csci2</sc> server.

<ol TYPE=I>

    <li>
	Create the directory <tt>lab2</tt> in your <tt>labs</tt> directory, then move to it (you can use the <tt>mv</tt> or <tt>pushd</tt> command in Unix to move to a directory).
    </li>

    <li>
	Perform LAB 3.1 - 3.4 and LAB 3.5 <i>Options</i> 2 &amp; 3.
    </li>

    <li>
	Use your editor to write the answers to the questions and exercises in
	<a href="http://web.stcloudstate.edu/aanda/cs201/Gaddis/7e/Labs/LM_Chapter03.pdf">Lab 2</a>
	in the file <tt>Lab2answers.txt</tt>
	locating it in directory <tt>lab2</tt></li>. Then submit the file to your lab2 dropbox in D2L.<br>
	As with all assignments submitted to a dropbox, your name, <sc>csci2</sc> login, assignment category &amp; number [e.g. Lab 2],
	and date must be included at the top of your file.
    </li>

    <li>
    When you are sure that each program is working correctly, use the <tt>script</tt> command to display first the source file, then execution, 
    of each lab assignment program.  The <tt><b>^D</b></tt> character will end the <tt>script</tt> session.<br>
    What you enter into your <tt>script</tt> session will look like this:
    <tt>
    <pre>
	&gt;script -a Lab2typescript.txt
	&gt;cat program1.cpp
	&gt;program1
	    (your input to program 1 is here)
	&gt;cat program2.cpp
	&gt;program2
	    (your input to program 2 is here)
	    .
	     .
	      .
	&gt;^D
    </pre>
    </tt>
    Submit <tt>Lab2typescript.txt</tt> to the D2L Dropbox.
    </li>

</ol>
Here are the authors' source files for this lab:
<ul>
    <li> <a href="http://web.stcloudstate.edu/aanda/cs201/Gaddis/7e/Labs/SourceCode/Lab3/batavg.cpp">batavg.cpp</a>
